00020 //-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
00021 // explanation of post_fixes:
00022 //   _O    : offset; this is the address where the register is located.
00023 //           if the register has more than 8 bits so that it is spread
00024 //           over more than one address this offset is the address of the
00025 //           8 LSBs. The next 8 bits are located at offset+1 and so on
00026 //
00027 //   _B    : for one-bit-registers this is the bit position inside the byte
00028 //           the value range is 0 to 7 where 0 is the LSB and 7 the MSB
00029 //
00030 //   _LSB  : for registers with several bits this value gives the position
00031 //           of the lowest bit inside the byte at the offset address
00032 //
00033 //   _MSB  : for registers with several bits this value gives the position
00034 //           of the highest bit at the offset address. This is always related
00035 //           to the offset address but if the value is 8 or higher the bit is
00036 //           placed at address offset+X.
00037 //
00038 //   _I    : this is the initialization value of the register which is inside
00039 //           after reset.
00040 //-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
